WEBVTT

00:00.024 --> 00:04.972
♪ Hey, why is it happening ♪

00:05.944 --> 00:08.652
♪ My heart is racing ♪

00:09.784 --> 00:13.792
♪ The world has fallen silent ♪

00:13.816 --> 00:18.572
♪ Hey, when I imagine you ♪

00:19.608 --> 00:22.636
♪ What kind of look ♪

00:23.640 --> 00:27.584
♪ Attracted me to you ♪

00:27.608 --> 00:30.880
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:30.904 --> 00:34.368
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:34.392 --> 00:39.640
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:39.640 --> 00:41.258
♪ I love you ♪

00:41.258 --> 00:44.736
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:44.760 --> 00:48.032
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:48.056 --> 00:53.728
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:53.752 --> 00:55.096
♪ I love you ♪

00:55.096 --> 00:58.432
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:58.456 --> 01:01.804
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:01.912 --> 01:07.109
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:07.109 --> 01:08.792
♪ I love you ♪

01:08.792 --> 01:12.192
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

01:12.216 --> 01:15.616
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:15.640 --> 01:21.216
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:21.240 --> 01:24.652
♪ I love you ♪

01:26.930 --> 01:27.720
=Love Me, Love My Voice=

01:27.720 --> 01:31.150
=Love Me, Love My Voice=
=Episode 5=

01:31.432 --> 01:34.203
(Thank you for escorting me
back to school today.)

01:35.022 --> 01:38.121
Let's get a feel
before we officially start recording.

01:39.542 --> 01:41.242
Save your energy for later.

01:42.382 --> 01:43.721
Mao.

01:44.861 --> 01:45.757
Yes?

01:45.781 --> 01:49.317
We'll start from the Section B.

01:49.341 --> 01:50.421
- Okay.
- Section B.

01:50.421 --> 01:50.998
Okay.

01:51.022 --> 01:52.918
Let's first try the chorus.

01:52.942 --> 01:54.641
I'll familiarize myself with lyrics.

02:01.792 --> 02:04.841
♪ Grinding the memories into ink ♪

02:04.841 --> 02:07.880
♪ And writing them on the paper ♪

02:07.904 --> 02:10.024
♪ The mirror and the person
are both gone ♪

02:10.024 --> 02:12.796
♪ Where could I ask for the return date ♪

02:12.862 --> 02:15.001
(He doesn't need
to look at the lyrics at all.)

02:15.061 --> 02:17.982
(This go-through
is just to make me more accustomed.)

02:17.984 --> 02:22.582
♪ Over millions of miles ♪

02:23.040 --> 02:26.888
♪ I laugh at the fame
and wealth of my life ♪

02:26.888 --> 02:28.960
♪ I picture it as a flower in the mirror ♪

02:28.960 --> 02:32.838
♪ It's hard to rival
a cup of tea in your hand ♪

02:32.862 --> 02:34.522
She feels nervous.

02:35.872 --> 02:37.576
♪ And we share joy and sorrow ♪

02:37.576 --> 02:40.200
♪ We drink down the past memories ♪

02:40.200 --> 02:44.936
♪ Being together from morning till night ♪

02:44.936 --> 02:48.444
♪ Or alone in the corner of the world ♪

02:48.444 --> 02:50.440
♪ Frost whitens the hair
in front of the forehead ♪

02:50.440 --> 02:55.496
♪ Looking at the world, where is my home ♪

02:55.496 --> 02:58.184
♪ I wish the clear frost
glitter in the moonlight ♪

02:58.184 --> 03:01.979
♪ Reflecting the couple in the mirror ♪

03:01.979 --> 03:07.302
♪ Return with you ♪

03:07.712 --> 03:13.276
♪ After being separated for half a life ♪

03:14.742 --> 03:16.838
The atmosphere is wonderful.

03:16.862 --> 03:19.118
Sheng, don't be nervous.

03:19.142 --> 03:19.757
Although I know

03:19.781 --> 03:21.118
suddenly being looked at by Mr. Mo

03:21.142 --> 03:23.121
may indeed make it hard for you
to stay calm,

03:23.262 --> 03:25.238
you just need to get used to it.

03:25.262 --> 03:26.762
That's enough.

03:28.061 --> 03:29.558
Let's do an official recording.

03:29.582 --> 03:31.238
Sheng, don't be nervous.

03:31.262 --> 03:33.398
Then we'll check out
where it needs improvement

03:33.422 --> 03:35.082
and fix it, alright?

03:35.142 --> 03:36.118
Wait a moment.

03:36.142 --> 03:38.601
I actually think
the chorus part is quite good.

03:38.661 --> 03:41.238
You sing "We drink from the same cup".

03:41.262 --> 03:43.196
I sing "And we share joy and sorrow".

03:43.661 --> 03:45.721
This is like a dialogue.

03:47.101 --> 03:48.797
See? He's so professional.

03:48.821 --> 03:49.962
Right.

03:50.582 --> 03:53.398
By the way, don't forget that
during Section B,

03:53.422 --> 03:56.281
- we take turns singing.
- Okay.

03:56.862 --> 04:00.281
Let's do it one more time.

04:01.702 --> 04:03.041
Mao.

04:36.302 --> 04:41.702
♪ Turning the years into a drifting boat ♪

04:41.726 --> 04:46.812
♪ Sailing through
the tumult and winding sorrow ♪

04:47.070 --> 04:52.232
♪ I fear that the past will be crushed
by the coming cold wind ♪

04:52.232 --> 04:58.338
♪ And stirred into
a piece of tranquil river water ♪

05:00.670 --> 05:05.917
♪ Touching the crack with my fingertips ♪

05:05.917 --> 05:11.027
♪ I dare not look at the haggard faces
and gray hair in the mirror ♪

05:11.027 --> 05:16.744
♪ After many years,
the longing remains as sharp ♪

05:16.744 --> 05:22.266
♪ And our shadows are thinner ♪

05:22.266 --> 05:25.576
♪ Grinding the memories into ink ♪

05:25.576 --> 05:28.144
♪ And writing them on the paper ♪

05:28.144 --> 05:30.248
♪ The mirror and the person
are both gone ♪

05:30.248 --> 05:32.968
♪ Where could I ask for the return date ♪

05:32.968 --> 05:36.138
♪ The bronze mirror shatters at farewell ♪

05:36.138 --> 05:38.312
♪ It's hard to convey the lovesickness ♪

05:38.312 --> 05:42.940
♪ Over millions of miles ♪

05:43.518 --> 05:47.080
♪ I laugh at the fame
and wealth of my life ♪

05:47.080 --> 05:49.059
♪ I picture it as a flower in the mirror ♪

05:49.059 --> 05:54.184
♪ It's hard to rival
a cup of tea in your hand ♪

05:54.184 --> 05:55.816
♪ We drink from the same cup ♪

05:55.816 --> 05:57.768
♪ And we share joy and sorrow ♪

05:57.768 --> 06:00.621
♪ We drink down the past memories ♪

06:00.621 --> 06:05.288
♪ Being together from morning till night ♪

06:05.288 --> 06:08.648
♪ Or alone in the corner of the world ♪

06:08.648 --> 06:10.655
♪ Frost whitens the hair
in front of the forehead ♪

06:10.655 --> 06:15.816
♪ Looking at the world, where is my home ♪

06:15.816 --> 06:18.420
♪ I wish the clear frost
glitter in the moonlight ♪

06:18.420 --> 06:22.142
♪ Reflecting the couple in the mirror ♪

06:22.142 --> 06:27.228
♪ Return with you ♪

06:27.870 --> 06:33.542
♪ After being separated for half a life ♪

06:33.741 --> 06:37.762
Finishing the Ode of Shanglin
with several strokes,

06:38.421 --> 06:43.438
I close the book and promise
to return with you in both lifetimes.

06:43.462 --> 06:45.998
(He actually added a monologue.)

06:46.022 --> 06:47.118
What's this?

06:47.142 --> 06:48.781
This is cheating.

06:48.781 --> 06:51.041
He absolutely prepared this beforehand.

06:51.518 --> 06:55.310
♪ I laugh at the fame
and wealth of my life ♪

06:55.310 --> 06:57.280
♪ I picture it as a flower in the mirror ♪

06:57.280 --> 07:02.280
♪ It's hard to rival
a cup of tea in your hand ♪

07:02.280 --> 07:03.976
♪ We drink from the same cup ♪

07:03.976 --> 07:05.916
♪ And we share joy and sorrow ♪

07:05.916 --> 07:08.657
♪ We drink down the past memories ♪

07:08.657 --> 07:13.096
♪ Being together from morning till night ♪

07:13.096 --> 07:16.645
♪ Or alone in the corner of the world ♪

07:16.645 --> 07:18.673
♪ Frost whitens the hair
in front of the forehead ♪

07:18.673 --> 07:23.784
♪ Looking at the world, where is my home ♪

07:23.784 --> 07:26.536
♪ I wish the clear frost
glitter in the moonlight ♪

07:26.536 --> 07:30.283
♪ Reflecting the couple in the mirror ♪

07:30.283 --> 07:35.646
♪ Return with you ♪

07:35.976 --> 07:42.908
♪ After being separated for half a life ♪

07:53.662 --> 07:59.004
♪ Turning the years into a drifting boat ♪

07:59.336 --> 08:04.435
♪ Sailing through
the tumult and winding sorrow ♪

08:04.435 --> 08:10.664
♪ The past has been rippling
and spilling over in the mind ♪

08:10.664 --> 08:15.452
♪ And the moonlight
brightens and dims softly ♪

08:16.094 --> 08:23.804
♪ And the moonlight
brightens and dims softly ♪

08:26.342 --> 08:29.961
Only when the world ceases to exist

08:30.022 --> 08:33.321
will I break up with you.

08:35.301 --> 08:37.397
I can't take it anymore.

08:37.421 --> 08:38.441
Okay, done.

08:40.342 --> 08:43.878
Awesome, Mo Qingcheng.
Your monologue is brilliant.

08:43.902 --> 08:46.118
I think as soon
as this version is released,

08:46.142 --> 08:48.598
it will instantly overshadow
all the previous covers.

08:48.622 --> 08:49.318
I agree.

08:49.342 --> 08:51.718
I bet if this version is released,
the download and play counts

08:51.742 --> 08:53.157
will break the record in three hours.

08:53.181 --> 08:55.198
You really underestimate him.

08:55.222 --> 08:58.642
I bet it'll break the record
in just one hour.

08:59.461 --> 09:00.921
Alright.

09:01.982 --> 09:03.362
What do you think?

09:03.742 --> 09:05.201
It's perfect.

09:07.301 --> 09:08.718
I mean,

09:08.742 --> 09:13.522
your singing and monologue
are all incredibly perfect.

09:14.781 --> 09:15.781
Thank you.

09:15.941 --> 09:18.961
Sheng, how is it? Are you touched?

09:19.301 --> 09:21.061
Your heart must be beating fast.

09:21.061 --> 09:24.201
I'm a guy, and I can hardly contain
my excitement, let alone a girl.

09:24.262 --> 09:25.917
You two bad guys.

09:25.941 --> 09:27.041
What's up?

09:27.862 --> 09:28.921
Nothing.

09:30.461 --> 09:33.522
- Let's go out and take a break.
- Okay.

09:35.181 --> 09:36.281
Here they come.

09:42.581 --> 09:43.478
Tell me,

09:43.502 --> 09:46.037
you've had the lines prepared, right?

09:46.061 --> 09:48.318
You waited for Sheng to come
so you could say them to her.

09:48.342 --> 09:49.722
I think so.

09:49.941 --> 09:51.757
Alright. No more joking.

09:51.781 --> 09:53.478
Otherwise, Sheng will think
it is a den of wolves

09:53.502 --> 09:54.972
and not dare to come again.

09:55.262 --> 09:57.602
Mao, what do you think?
Is this version good?

09:57.862 --> 09:58.998
It's pretty good,

09:59.022 --> 10:03.002
especially those lines
you improvised on the spot.

10:03.461 --> 10:06.118
Sheng, have some water first.

10:06.142 --> 10:07.437
There are some lines

10:07.461 --> 10:09.561
that we might need
to sing separately later.

10:10.061 --> 10:11.081
Okay.

10:14.622 --> 10:15.642
Over there.

10:21.461 --> 10:22.397
Great.

10:22.421 --> 10:25.281
It's so impressive.

10:28.541 --> 10:30.002
Do you need anything?

10:30.541 --> 10:33.281
- I'd like a cup of water.
- Okay.

10:39.541 --> 10:40.461
Be careful. It's hot.

10:40.461 --> 10:41.142
Thank you.

10:41.142 --> 10:42.882
The environment here is good, right?

10:43.421 --> 10:46.762
This is my first time
in such a big recording studio.

10:51.781 --> 10:53.921
Shengshengman?

10:55.541 --> 10:57.118
Don't worry. I'll keep it secret.

10:57.142 --> 10:58.358
It's professional ethics.

10:58.382 --> 11:01.122
I'm the new intern here.
My name is Xiyou.

11:01.541 --> 11:03.118
I just heard

11:03.142 --> 11:06.002
you were singing with Mr. Mo.

11:08.061 --> 11:10.041
You're the one who...

11:10.181 --> 11:12.681
I'm the one who made the Weibo post.

11:13.821 --> 11:16.242
How did you come to know Mr. Mo?

11:18.742 --> 11:22.002
I just ran into him.

11:23.142 --> 11:25.421
(I can't exactly say that one morning, )

11:25.421 --> 11:27.622
(he somehow entered my audio room)

11:27.622 --> 11:29.402
(and taught me to cook, right?)

11:29.622 --> 11:32.602
You can't tell me. I get it.

11:34.262 --> 11:34.982
I have another...

11:34.982 --> 11:36.122
Shengshengman,

11:38.262 --> 11:39.561
it's your turn now.

11:41.102 --> 11:42.242
Thank you.

11:45.781 --> 11:47.362
Should I go in now?

11:47.661 --> 11:49.882
Sorry, I was late today.

11:51.742 --> 11:54.242
I thought you weren't coming today.

11:55.022 --> 11:56.762
I almost couldn't make it.

11:57.581 --> 12:01.561
- Is it because of work?
- Yes.

12:05.941 --> 12:07.321
Are you whispering?

12:07.461 --> 12:08.637
No, not at all.

12:08.661 --> 12:10.482
I was drinking water, and he called me.

12:10.581 --> 12:12.677
You don't have to explain it to me.

12:12.701 --> 12:15.642
You two have one more minute
before wrapping up, okay?

12:21.142 --> 12:23.642
- I'll go in first.
- Okay.

12:30.421 --> 12:31.642
How is it?

12:32.421 --> 12:34.838
- Let her prepare first, Mao.
- Okay.

12:34.862 --> 12:37.581
She simply went out to drink water,
and he followed.

12:37.581 --> 12:39.242
He was afraid she would leave.

12:39.581 --> 12:41.797
She wouldn't.
Her backpack is still here.

12:41.821 --> 12:43.362
It's so heavy.

12:43.541 --> 12:45.598
Her bag is so heavy,
and she still brought us snacks.

12:45.622 --> 12:47.242
She is so nice.

12:47.421 --> 12:48.872
I think the backpack
is also full of food.

12:48.872 --> 12:51.080
It must be stuffed by her parents
as she is returning to school.

12:51.080 --> 12:53.781
It happened to me before. My parents
prepared a huge bag of food for me back then.

12:53.781 --> 12:55.441
I was exhausted.

12:56.022 --> 12:57.797
I didn't carry a backpack
when I was in school.

12:57.821 --> 12:59.078
Yeah.

12:59.102 --> 13:00.998
That's why
I didn't get to eat any snacks from you.

13:01.022 --> 13:02.441
It is quite heavy.

13:03.421 --> 13:06.441
- Mao, shall we start?
- Okay.

13:07.821 --> 13:11.402
With him supervising,
it will take at least 20 rounds.

13:11.701 --> 13:14.277
I guess it won't be done
any sooner than 6 PM.

13:14.301 --> 13:15.677
I'll go find something to eat first.

13:15.701 --> 13:17.238
I'm starving.

13:17.262 --> 13:18.561
I'm going too.

13:19.262 --> 13:21.681
- I'll take a nap somewhere.
- I'll go to the bathroom.

13:23.222 --> 13:24.277
Keep going.

13:24.301 --> 13:26.081
Close the door.

13:27.022 --> 13:30.718
Sheng, let's work hard
and finish it in one go.

13:30.742 --> 13:32.397
So you won't have to come back.

13:32.421 --> 13:33.842
Okay, no problem.

13:34.382 --> 13:36.642
Keep going. Let's get started.

14:13.061 --> 14:14.797
Sheng, overall, it's pretty good.

14:14.821 --> 14:18.081
- Try to tone down your emotions a bit.
- Okay.

14:18.701 --> 14:19.701
Keep going.

14:44.022 --> 14:45.242
Mr. Mo,

14:45.821 --> 14:49.478
from my perspective
as a professional singer,

14:49.502 --> 14:51.961
this is already very good.

14:52.862 --> 14:54.762
I think it's already perfect.

14:55.382 --> 14:56.882
I am okay with it either.

15:02.142 --> 15:04.478
Sheng, this version is good enough.

15:04.502 --> 15:06.281
Really? Is it really good?

15:06.742 --> 15:07.637
It's excellent.

15:07.661 --> 15:09.198
Everyone thinks it's good.

15:09.222 --> 15:10.842
Good job. You can come out now.

15:11.622 --> 15:13.122
Okay, thank you.

15:14.541 --> 15:16.238
Good job. Great.

15:16.262 --> 15:17.262
- It's very good.
- Right.

15:17.262 --> 15:17.862
It is not easy.

15:17.862 --> 15:20.002
Why does it sound so good?

15:23.622 --> 15:24.277
Great job.

15:24.301 --> 15:25.718
Well done.

15:25.742 --> 15:26.541
You sang it so well.

15:26.541 --> 15:28.598
Take a rest. You must be tired.

15:28.622 --> 15:30.637
His standards are usually high.

15:30.661 --> 15:33.161
You'll get used to it.
Don't mind. You sang really well.

15:33.461 --> 15:34.844
I did what I should do.

15:35.301 --> 15:36.321
See?

15:36.541 --> 15:38.757
You two are definitely perfectionists.

15:38.781 --> 15:40.397
I'm starving.

15:40.421 --> 15:42.238
All I can think about

15:42.262 --> 15:44.681
is hot pot, barbecue, and grilled meat.

15:44.781 --> 15:45.821
I feel even more hungry now.

15:45.821 --> 15:49.482
You don't understand.
It is what we call a spiritual exchange.

15:49.661 --> 15:51.598
All good relationships

15:51.622 --> 15:54.998
have to start
with the exchange of beautiful voices.

15:55.022 --> 15:56.277
Stop nagging.

15:56.301 --> 15:59.277
I heard that you had been communicating
for two months

15:59.301 --> 16:01.002
before deciding to meet offline.

16:01.382 --> 16:03.961
Can't Sheng shut you up
with all the food she brought?

16:04.181 --> 16:05.602
I almost forgot.

16:05.781 --> 16:06.437
Sheng,

16:06.461 --> 16:08.238
do you have time tonight
to have dinner with us?

16:08.262 --> 16:10.002
Tonight?

16:10.061 --> 16:11.838
Tonight, I have to return to school.

16:11.862 --> 16:14.321
I probably won't be able
to have dinner with all of you.

16:15.502 --> 16:18.312
This is your first time here,
and you are in our studio.

16:18.312 --> 16:20.198
Letting you leave
on an empty stomach isn't good.

16:20.222 --> 16:21.238
- Yeah.
- Exactly.

16:21.262 --> 16:23.718
This isn't our way of treating guests.

16:23.742 --> 16:24.677
You are our only guest.

16:24.701 --> 16:25.742
We're all hosts here.

16:25.742 --> 16:27.801
We must treat you well.

16:28.181 --> 16:29.142
There is no need for that.

16:29.142 --> 16:30.917
Sheng, just let us treat you.

16:30.941 --> 16:32.718
We really don't dare make fun of him.

16:32.742 --> 16:34.078
Now that you're here,

16:34.102 --> 16:36.281
it's so much fun
that we can all tease him.

16:36.502 --> 16:37.838
You dare to joke about him?

16:37.862 --> 16:40.522
Aren't you afraid that he'll cut you up?

16:40.821 --> 16:42.081
Stop saying that.

16:42.142 --> 16:44.838
It's getting late.
I should go back to school.

16:44.862 --> 16:47.557
We can have dinner together next time.

16:47.581 --> 16:50.281
We'll see you off.

16:50.342 --> 16:52.321
I'm on your way. I'll accompany you.

16:53.461 --> 16:55.397
Then, we won't see you off.

16:55.421 --> 16:56.921
You won't stay for dinner?

17:00.542 --> 17:02.078
- Take care.
- Let me carry it for you.

17:02.102 --> 17:03.562
- No need.
- It's okay.

17:05.461 --> 17:07.857
You guys wrap up. We'll go first.

17:07.881 --> 17:09.997
- You are welcome. We are supposed to do it.
- You can leave it to us.

17:10.021 --> 17:11.721
Just ignore us.

17:12.302 --> 17:13.402
Okay, let's go.

17:13.701 --> 17:14.677
Mao,

17:14.701 --> 17:16.342
keep all the tracks for me.

17:16.342 --> 17:18.161
And pick up the vocals for me first.

17:20.302 --> 17:21.318
Someone is missing you.

17:21.342 --> 17:23.062
- Goodbye.
- Thank you for your hard work.

17:23.062 --> 17:24.062
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

17:24.062 --> 17:25.481
Take care.

17:26.822 --> 17:29.961
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

17:30.582 --> 17:32.642
You scared me.

17:42.741 --> 17:45.078
This backpack is pretty heavy.
I can carry it myself.

17:45.102 --> 17:46.282
It's okay.

17:49.661 --> 17:51.402
It's not very late yet.

17:51.622 --> 17:53.201
Is your school far from here?

17:53.542 --> 17:54.397
Not too far.

17:54.421 --> 17:57.602
If the bus comes on time,
it will take about 20 minutes.

17:57.981 --> 17:59.001
That's good.

18:01.142 --> 18:04.761
(It's really impolite to let him
carry my backpack when we first met.)

18:05.622 --> 18:07.078
They were too noisy just now.

18:07.102 --> 18:08.278
If you're not in a hurry,

18:08.302 --> 18:11.196
I'll accompany you to have a simple meal
before escorting you back.

18:12.622 --> 18:14.076
What would you like to eat?

18:17.382 --> 18:19.362
How about bamboo shoot soup?

18:21.021 --> 18:23.602
If you have no objection,
let's have bamboo shoot soup.

18:24.582 --> 18:26.521
This season is just right for having it.

18:27.501 --> 18:28.501
Let's go.

18:37.382 --> 18:39.197
(Back Alley)
Take care. Come again!

18:39.221 --> 18:40.521
Alright, goodbye.

18:42.116 --> 18:46.236
(Back Alley Private Cuisine)

18:48.421 --> 18:49.481
Welcome.

18:49.701 --> 18:51.481
- This way, please.
- Okay.

18:52.902 --> 18:54.278
Mr. Mo, you're quite early today.

18:54.302 --> 18:55.362
Right.

18:56.822 --> 18:58.237
- Who will do the ordering?
- I will.

18:58.261 --> 19:00.397
The bamboo shoot soup takes a while.
Let's start with that.

19:00.421 --> 19:02.518
Alright, take your time with the menu.

19:02.542 --> 19:04.038
I'll tell the chef
to start on that for you.

19:04.062 --> 19:04.981
Okay, thank you, Wang.

19:04.981 --> 19:06.082
You're welcome.

19:06.582 --> 19:08.078
Start with the bamboo shoot soup.

19:08.102 --> 19:09.441
Got it.

19:10.701 --> 19:13.308
I'm not familiar with this place.
You should do the ordering.

19:13.992 --> 19:15.681
Then I'll order for us.

19:16.902 --> 19:18.882
Let's have a few specialties.

19:20.941 --> 19:23.957
Three meat dishes and one vegetable dish.
And the bamboo shoot soup.

19:23.981 --> 19:24.782
Isn't that too much?

19:24.782 --> 19:26.701
Two meat dishes and one vegetable dish
should be enough.

19:26.701 --> 19:29.724
If need be,
order an additional cold dish.

19:29.822 --> 19:30.921
Grilled gluten?

19:34.102 --> 19:36.842
Okay. Beverage or tea?

19:37.461 --> 19:38.642
Tea.

19:38.741 --> 19:39.598
What kind of tea?

19:39.622 --> 19:41.921
Chrysanthemum? Pu-erh?

19:42.582 --> 19:43.602
Either will do.

19:44.102 --> 19:45.362
Pu-erh.

19:46.221 --> 19:47.882
Okay. Wait a second.

19:51.822 --> 19:54.082
One of these...

20:01.181 --> 20:02.282
Thank you.

20:04.461 --> 20:05.957
This place is like our dining hall.

20:05.981 --> 20:07.358
When we're too busy,

20:07.382 --> 20:08.518
we simply notify the boss,

20:08.542 --> 20:10.521
and the food will be delivered
to our door.

20:11.342 --> 20:13.642
I see you and the boss
are familiar with each other.

20:30.902 --> 20:33.042
How does it taste? Is it to your liking?

20:34.181 --> 20:36.118
The bamboo shoot soup here
is very tasty.

20:36.142 --> 20:37.842
I particularly enjoy it.

20:38.741 --> 20:39.878
Me too.

20:39.902 --> 20:43.318
But usually, it's my parents
who cook it for me at home.

20:43.342 --> 20:44.637
I rarely eat out.

20:44.661 --> 20:45.957
My parents were very busy with work.

20:45.981 --> 20:48.921
It's mostly just me cooking.

20:49.181 --> 20:51.598
After graduation,
I started living with Juemei.

20:51.622 --> 20:54.441
When we were too lazy to cook,
we went out to eat together.

20:55.902 --> 20:57.362
Have you tried cooking it?

20:59.461 --> 21:00.358
No.

21:00.382 --> 21:01.761
It's simple.

21:01.822 --> 21:04.038
Blanch chunks of fresh bamboo shoots
in hot water first.

21:04.062 --> 21:06.677
Then use cold water to soak salty meat
and dried bamboo shoots

21:06.701 --> 21:08.842
to remove the saltiness.

21:11.622 --> 21:12.642
Thank you.

21:13.782 --> 21:16.957
Put the scallion and ginger
in the cold water.

21:16.981 --> 21:19.961
After the water boils,
add the salty meat and ribs to it.

21:20.142 --> 21:22.642
But sometimes
I also like to add salty pig's feet.

21:23.741 --> 21:25.997
When the soup is turned
into such a milky white one,

21:26.021 --> 21:29.322
turn to low heat
and cook for another hour.

21:30.142 --> 21:32.082
What about the tied tofu skin?

21:32.542 --> 21:33.642
Don't rush.

21:33.704 --> 21:36.518
Finally, add the tied tofu skin
and simmer for a quarter of an hour

21:36.542 --> 21:38.157
before sprinkling some chopped chives.

21:38.181 --> 21:39.521
Then it can be served.

21:44.902 --> 21:48.562
You seem to enjoy talking about recipes.

21:51.701 --> 21:53.362
Do you want to hear the truth?

21:54.741 --> 21:55.761
Sure.

21:57.382 --> 22:01.642
Actually, I don't really know
what to say to you.

22:02.021 --> 22:05.082
But it seems
that you don't resist recipes.

22:07.021 --> 22:08.477
Of course not.

22:08.501 --> 22:10.118
I actually really enjoy them.

22:10.142 --> 22:12.518
Every time you talk about recipes,
I take notes seriously,

22:12.542 --> 22:15.001
thinking there will be a chance
for me to try them out.

22:15.622 --> 22:16.642
Really?

22:17.142 --> 22:18.721
I'm glad I helped.

22:20.382 --> 22:21.402
Are you full?

22:22.021 --> 22:23.082
Yes.

22:24.021 --> 22:27.201
- Bill, please.
- Coming.

22:29.021 --> 22:31.721
Here. It's a total of 187 yuan.

22:32.342 --> 22:35.241
Is this your new employee?
She's so young.

22:35.701 --> 22:37.921
No. She's still a student.

22:38.701 --> 22:41.278
It's the first time you've come
with a girl. I'll give you a discount.

22:41.302 --> 22:43.681
That's 150 yuan.

22:45.062 --> 22:46.642
- Thank you.
- Here you go.

22:48.782 --> 22:50.481
- It's done.
- Okay.

22:51.261 --> 22:51.917
Thank you.

22:51.941 --> 22:53.001
You're welcome.

22:53.981 --> 22:55.201
Thank you.

22:55.862 --> 22:57.082
You're welcome.

22:57.741 --> 23:00.717
Well, let's go then.

23:00.741 --> 23:02.997
Your school is far away from here.

23:03.021 --> 23:05.681
- We need to hurry.
- Okay.

23:10.622 --> 23:11.501
Let me carry that.

23:11.501 --> 23:12.542
- It's okay.
- It is too heavy.

23:12.542 --> 23:13.677
You can put on your scarf.

23:13.701 --> 23:16.042
Mo Qingcheng?

23:17.021 --> 23:18.161
Sheng.

23:19.302 --> 23:21.397
Didn't you say you were going to
escort her back to school?

23:21.421 --> 23:22.981
But it's been 40 or 50 minutes already,

23:22.981 --> 23:25.038
and you are still
around the recording studio.

23:25.062 --> 23:27.241
Stop talking, you silly.

23:27.302 --> 23:29.642
The food here is pretty good, right?

23:30.221 --> 23:31.882
You can come here often.

23:32.261 --> 23:34.038
You guys had bamboo shoot soup?

23:34.062 --> 23:34.881
I thought we were friends.

23:34.881 --> 23:36.902
I've been talking about it for days
and you wouldn't come with me.

23:36.902 --> 23:38.957
He has Sheng now
and has no time for you.

23:38.981 --> 23:39.917
How about I eat with you?

23:39.941 --> 23:40.741
Okay, then it's settled.

23:40.741 --> 23:42.358
Don't just stand there. Come and sit.

23:42.382 --> 23:44.322
- Coming.
- Here.

23:44.461 --> 23:45.798
You two keep going.

23:45.822 --> 23:47.602
Just pretend I weren't here.

23:49.181 --> 23:50.282
Then let's go.

23:51.862 --> 23:52.997
We're leaving. Enjoy your meal.

23:53.021 --> 23:54.181
Escort her back safely.

23:54.181 --> 23:54.822
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

23:54.822 --> 23:55.501
Goodbye, Sheng.

23:55.501 --> 23:56.181
See you, Sheng.

23:56.181 --> 23:57.437
We're leaving, Wang.

23:57.461 --> 23:58.157
Wang,

23:58.181 --> 23:58.981
we need to order now.

23:58.981 --> 24:00.118
I'm coming.

24:00.142 --> 24:01.142
We want bamboo shoot soup too.

24:01.142 --> 24:01.741
No problem.

24:01.741 --> 24:03.142
I'll have them
start preparing yours first.

24:03.142 --> 24:04.700
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

24:05.622 --> 24:07.157
They're used to joking with me.

24:07.181 --> 24:08.802
Don't take it to heart.

24:08.902 --> 24:09.637
It's fine.

24:09.661 --> 24:12.761
They like to joke around online.

24:13.421 --> 24:14.221
Give me the backpack.

24:14.221 --> 24:15.282
It's fine.

24:15.862 --> 24:17.521
Really, it's fine.

24:17.582 --> 24:20.082
This doesn't weigh much for me at all.

24:20.501 --> 24:22.118
I'm returning to school today.

24:22.142 --> 24:24.917
So I brought more things than usual,
making it heavier.

24:24.941 --> 24:27.562
I feel bad for having you carry it.

24:30.302 --> 24:32.921
It's getting dark.
I'll go back to school myself.

24:33.501 --> 24:34.598
It's because it's getting dark

24:34.622 --> 24:37.961
that I want to escort you back.
Let's go.

24:48.421 --> 24:49.681
My bus is here.

25:01.782 --> 25:03.122
Give me the backpack.

25:29.981 --> 25:32.241
It's from the hospital... Just a moment.

25:32.701 --> 25:34.802
I'm okay. Take your time.

25:47.142 --> 25:49.441
I thought

25:49.622 --> 25:52.481
you were good at dubbing
and didn't like singing.

25:53.302 --> 25:54.362
Why is that?

25:55.622 --> 25:57.358
I rarely hear you sing.

25:57.382 --> 25:59.157
Your singing is so beautiful.

25:59.181 --> 26:02.402
Why don't you sing but only do dubbing?

26:03.021 --> 26:06.562
Singing takes more effort.

26:07.421 --> 26:09.961
I feel dubbing is more tiring.

26:11.562 --> 26:14.002
Every profession
produces its own leading practitioner.

26:14.582 --> 26:18.282
It's better for us
to do what we are good at.

26:18.941 --> 26:23.362
- But your singing is really beautiful.
- Thanks.

26:27.582 --> 26:30.882
The path to our recording studio
has nice scenery.

26:33.622 --> 26:36.642
I'll take you for a walk
next time you come again.

26:50.432 --> 26:55.287
♪ There is a voice
that soaks the green plums ♪

26:56.448 --> 27:01.303
♪ There is a voice
that wrinkles the blue sky ♪

27:02.496 --> 27:06.568
♪ Shedding an invisible spring rain ♪

27:06.568 --> 27:13.244
♪ The world is drunk at a timid moment ♪

27:14.432 --> 27:19.955
♪ We talk and laugh
as if we are holding hands ♪

27:19.955 --> 27:26.376
♪ We stay silent
like falling behind the sunset ♪

27:26.376 --> 27:30.472
♪ That moment is still lingering ♪

27:30.472 --> 27:36.988
♪ When our eyes meet,
all vanish into nothing ♪

27:39.232 --> 27:45.928
♪ You flow through my heart like a river ♪

27:45.952 --> 27:51.432
♪ Echoing with the constant gentleness
of the bright moon ♪

27:51.552 --> 27:55.016
♪ Looking back
among fleeting and everlasting moments ♪

27:55.016 --> 27:57.984
♪ We embrace as we look around ♪

27:57.984 --> 28:03.528
♪ Each sound is a promise of forever
to a lifetime ♪

28:03.528 --> 28:09.212
♪ You linger in my dreams
countless times ♪

28:09.504 --> 28:15.420
♪ Whenever I see you,
my heart flutters a thousand times ♪

28:17.062 --> 28:18.197
Gu Sheng?

28:18.221 --> 28:19.558
When did you come back?

28:19.582 --> 28:20.961
This afternoon.

28:23.822 --> 28:25.122
Not bad.

28:26.261 --> 28:27.677
You misunderstood.

28:27.701 --> 28:30.082
I did? So he is your brother?

28:31.102 --> 28:32.038
No.

28:32.062 --> 28:33.917
Then I didn't misunderstand.

28:33.941 --> 28:35.362
I won't disturb you.

28:40.661 --> 28:43.038
I've arrived.

28:43.062 --> 28:44.201
Thank you.

28:44.421 --> 28:46.042
Okay. See you next time.

28:46.941 --> 28:48.161
See you.

28:48.622 --> 28:50.362
Go inside. I should go too.

28:51.021 --> 28:53.001
Have a safe journey.

28:59.382 --> 29:00.582
(It's so heavy.)

29:00.582 --> 29:02.677
(If I knew
he would carry it all the way, )

29:02.701 --> 29:04.721
(I definitely wouldn't bring
so many snacks.)

29:15.782 --> 29:18.441
What are you doing
standing there, Sheng?

29:23.501 --> 29:24.921
Why are you doing here?

29:27.181 --> 29:28.157
How did you feel to see him?

29:28.181 --> 29:30.161
Were you nervous or excited?

29:32.382 --> 29:33.961
Yes, I was excited.

29:34.902 --> 29:36.717
Juemei told me on WeChat,

29:36.741 --> 29:38.822
saying Qiang Qingci personally
escorted you to school.

29:38.822 --> 29:40.642
Is he handsome?

29:43.261 --> 29:44.721
He is not handsome?

29:44.782 --> 29:45.917
But it doesn't matter.

29:45.941 --> 29:47.882
Anyway, you don't judge by appearances.

29:50.302 --> 29:51.362
Let me help you.

29:52.661 --> 29:54.322
What's in it? It's so heavy.

29:55.221 --> 29:57.237
Meat mooncakes, egg yolk pastry,

29:57.261 --> 29:59.237
duck gizzards, duck necks, chips,

29:59.261 --> 30:01.558
deboned chicken feet, dried pork,

30:01.582 --> 30:04.521
and daily nuts.

30:06.221 --> 30:10.518
Does your mother fatten you up?

30:10.542 --> 30:11.677
No way.

30:11.701 --> 30:13.437
It's just that all four of my brothers

30:13.461 --> 30:14.741
each bought me some snacks.

30:14.741 --> 30:16.062
I couldn't choose, right?

30:16.062 --> 30:18.042
So I brought all the snacks. Let's go.

30:19.382 --> 30:20.441
Is he handsome?

30:21.701 --> 30:23.802
He seems alright.

30:27.701 --> 30:28.961
Mo Qingcheng?

30:29.701 --> 30:30.882
Mr. Lin.

30:31.461 --> 30:32.421
It really is you.

30:32.421 --> 30:33.717
Long time no see.

30:33.741 --> 30:35.558
It's been years since you graduated.

30:35.582 --> 30:37.917
Good. You're looking more spirited.

30:37.941 --> 30:40.201
You too. You are still charming.

30:40.701 --> 30:41.798
How's your health?

30:41.822 --> 30:42.758
I'm quite well.

30:42.782 --> 30:44.558
Do you know about the School of Media?

30:44.582 --> 30:46.078
The School of Media?

30:46.102 --> 30:48.878
I do. It's a newly established school.

30:48.902 --> 30:50.878
It used to belong
to the School of Literature.

30:50.902 --> 30:52.758
It has been formed for only a few years.

30:52.782 --> 30:53.838
No wonder

30:53.862 --> 30:56.062
I don't recall hearing about it
when I was studying.

30:56.062 --> 30:57.322
That's right.

30:57.582 --> 31:00.161
Why do you want to know
about the School of Media?

31:00.941 --> 31:03.882
I happen to have a junior there.

31:04.582 --> 31:05.761
A junior.

31:06.342 --> 31:07.717
Mr. Lin, please excuse me.

31:07.741 --> 31:08.677
I'll head back now.

31:08.701 --> 31:11.518
Okay, take care.
Come by when you have time.

31:11.542 --> 31:12.078
Stay in touch.

31:12.102 --> 31:13.261
Alright. Goodbye.

31:13.261 --> 31:14.157
Take care.

31:14.181 --> 31:14.997
Thank you.

31:15.021 --> 31:16.042
Goodbye.

31:16.501 --> 31:18.318
Juemei is tall

31:18.342 --> 31:20.721
and quite imposing
when he is not joking.

31:20.782 --> 31:22.652
He's more imposing than in the videos.

31:23.021 --> 31:25.758
Why don't you join me
at an event next time?

31:25.782 --> 31:27.237
Something is going on between you.

31:27.261 --> 31:28.598
No, there isn't.

31:28.622 --> 31:29.758
Don't talk nonsense.

31:29.782 --> 31:30.782
Are you sure?

31:30.782 --> 31:33.421
He even let you
eavesdrop on an internal event.

31:33.421 --> 31:35.197
That was because...

31:35.221 --> 31:36.501
What are you up there for?

31:36.501 --> 31:37.802
I'm tidying up the bed.

31:39.461 --> 31:43.038
Anyway, I feel
that Qiang Qingci has feelings for you.

31:43.062 --> 31:45.882
He even escorted you back to school.

31:49.302 --> 31:50.761
He did it out of politeness.

31:52.421 --> 31:53.518
Politeness?

31:53.542 --> 31:55.822
So he took a bus for more than 20 stops,

31:55.822 --> 31:58.798
which covered almost an entire bus line,
out of pure politeness?

31:58.822 --> 32:01.342
That was really an unprecedented level
of politeness.

32:01.342 --> 32:03.481
I'll have to go to the music club later.

32:04.822 --> 32:07.021
Just take your time to think it over
if he is interested in you.

32:07.021 --> 32:07.701
I'm late.

32:07.701 --> 32:09.562
And if you two actually get together...

32:12.382 --> 32:15.402
It's more like
something is going on between you two.

32:17.261 --> 32:19.402
You sent her back to school, and then?

32:19.582 --> 32:20.957
That's the end?

32:20.981 --> 32:22.001
Yes.

32:24.142 --> 32:25.402
Look at him.

32:43.421 --> 32:45.842
Why would you snoop
on someone else's phone?

32:46.021 --> 32:47.157
What a bad habit.

32:47.181 --> 32:49.921
It seems like
you haven't connected to the Wi-Fi.

32:55.342 --> 32:58.798
You have to strike
while the iron is hot.

32:58.822 --> 32:59.582
That's right.

32:59.582 --> 33:00.637
You are a doctor, after all.

33:00.661 --> 33:02.838
You have to live your day
as if it were 36 hours.

33:02.862 --> 33:04.437
You better use the new year's holiday

33:04.461 --> 33:05.637
and pursue the girl

33:05.661 --> 33:07.397
until you make her happy
with one fell swoop.

33:07.421 --> 33:09.838
Then, next year, you can bring her home
as your girlfriend.

33:09.862 --> 33:12.042
Right. And the year after that,
you propose to her.

33:12.221 --> 33:13.437
You're rushing things.

33:13.461 --> 33:14.481
I'm not.

33:19.296 --> 33:21.608
♪ It's hard to convey the lovesickness ♪

33:21.608 --> 33:25.728
♪ Over millions of miles ♪

33:26.021 --> 33:27.122
You're back.

33:29.062 --> 33:32.282
I want to listen to the song
I recorded this afternoon.

33:34.102 --> 33:34.957
It's not done yet.

33:34.981 --> 33:37.402
I just selected the vocals
and haven't done the mixdown.

33:38.062 --> 33:39.397
I'm not feeling very well lately.

33:39.421 --> 33:40.798
I really don't have the energy.

33:40.822 --> 33:42.122
Wait a little longer.

33:42.501 --> 33:44.282
You should take some medicine.

33:44.382 --> 33:45.237
I can do it myself.

33:45.261 --> 33:46.798
You'll do it yourself?

33:46.822 --> 33:49.562
I haven't seen you
personally work on anything for years.

33:50.302 --> 33:52.118
You are sick, and it's the new year.

33:52.142 --> 33:53.598
I should let you get some rest.

33:53.622 --> 33:54.842
Are you sure?

33:56.342 --> 33:58.722
- Then I'll leave it to you.
- No problem.

33:58.981 --> 33:59.997
Dress warmly.

34:00.021 --> 34:01.242
Okay.

34:04.672 --> 34:08.232
♪ Grinding the memories into ink ♪

34:08.232 --> 34:10.696
♪ And writing them on the paper ♪

34:10.696 --> 34:13.564
♪ The mirror and the person
are both gone ♪

34:14.581 --> 34:15.517
He is taking medicine.

34:15.541 --> 34:16.838
What's wrong, Mao?

34:16.862 --> 34:18.001
Are you okay?

34:18.101 --> 34:20.402
I got a cold.

34:21.382 --> 34:22.878
You should rest more.

34:22.902 --> 34:24.158
Rest? Sure.

34:24.182 --> 34:25.477
There are clothes at my place.

34:25.501 --> 34:27.162
Put them on later.

34:28.662 --> 34:29.682
By the way,

34:30.742 --> 34:31.997
what happened today?

34:32.021 --> 34:33.921
Why is he
doing post-production himself?

34:37.421 --> 34:41.318
Mao, don't you think
that Qiang Qingci was especially kind

34:41.342 --> 34:42.718
to Shengshengman,

34:42.742 --> 34:47.121
who came for the recording today?

34:47.342 --> 34:48.961
Yes, you are right.

34:50.262 --> 34:53.001
Didn't you say
it was their second meeting today?

34:53.061 --> 34:57.477
What if they fell in love
at first sight?

34:57.501 --> 34:58.878
It doesn't seem like it.

34:58.902 --> 35:01.362
Isn't Qiang Qingci a slow starter?

35:02.222 --> 35:05.362
In the beginning, we all thought so.

35:10.461 --> 35:13.041
Qiang Qingci is really unfathomable.

35:14.862 --> 35:17.162
Pretending to be profound.

35:17.302 --> 35:18.402
Let's drink.

35:55.148 --> 35:57.404
(Mixdown for Return with You)

35:59.148 --> 36:01.500
(Mixdown)

36:04.181 --> 36:07.228
(Chat history with Shengshengman)

36:12.302 --> 36:15.037
(Should I ask if he has arrived?)

36:15.061 --> 36:16.521
(Maybe not?)

36:17.061 --> 36:21.322
(Is it a bit strange to ask
if we're not very familiar?)

36:23.222 --> 36:24.441
Gu Sheng.

36:25.342 --> 36:27.041
Goodness!

36:28.182 --> 36:30.842
If they fell over, I would have to
help you for a while.

36:31.021 --> 36:32.601
Why are you here?

36:33.021 --> 36:34.198
To pick you up.

36:34.222 --> 36:36.278
The club leader asked me
to fetch you on my way back.

36:36.302 --> 36:38.517
Otherwise,
it would be a long walk for you.

36:38.541 --> 36:40.117
And it's not worth taking a taxi.

36:40.141 --> 36:42.081
You got a new bike?

36:42.421 --> 36:44.678
The old one was always
running out of power halfway.

36:44.702 --> 36:46.397
So I gritted my teeth and got a new one.

36:46.421 --> 36:48.222
I heard it can be used for ten years.

36:48.222 --> 36:49.282
Really?

36:52.782 --> 36:53.798
What are you looking at?

36:53.822 --> 36:55.802
You are blushing.

36:55.941 --> 36:56.838
Am I?

36:56.862 --> 36:59.838
Who are you thinking of?
You are smiling so radiantly.

36:59.862 --> 37:02.802
- Not at all. It's hot.
- If you say so.

37:03.061 --> 37:04.061
Done.

37:06.581 --> 37:08.001
Get on.

37:10.141 --> 37:11.037
Let's go.

37:11.061 --> 37:12.682
Hold tight. Off we go.

37:19.101 --> 37:20.077
Thank you, everyone.

37:20.101 --> 37:21.437
Let's take a quick break.

37:21.461 --> 37:23.441
I'll sing with you later.

37:24.501 --> 37:25.101
We are back.

37:25.101 --> 37:27.238
Thank goodness
someone is replacing me now.

37:27.262 --> 37:29.081
My throat is going to hurt.

37:30.342 --> 37:31.278
Hello, everyone.

37:31.302 --> 37:32.957
Next, our club's Shengshengman

37:32.981 --> 37:34.397
will continue to sing with you.

37:34.421 --> 37:36.678
Just wait a moment. Here.

37:36.702 --> 37:39.722
Where is Off Key?
Isn't he supposed to be here too?

37:40.222 --> 37:41.641
He went on a date.

37:41.822 --> 37:45.182
He said it took him 20 years
to be confessed to for the first time,

37:45.182 --> 37:47.382
and he had to go to that date.

37:47.382 --> 37:48.961
Then we should bless him.

37:49.541 --> 37:50.742
Don't push yourself too hard.

37:50.742 --> 37:52.638
It should be about time
after you sing two more songs.

37:52.662 --> 37:54.198
I'm going to log into my own account.

37:54.222 --> 37:55.932
I'll get you something to drink.

38:02.021 --> 38:04.561
Hello, everyone. I am Shengshengman.

38:07.541 --> 38:08.682
(I'm home now.)

38:12.262 --> 38:15.601
Sorry, I have to make a call first.

38:21.061 --> 38:24.722
(That's great. Thank you
for escorting me back to school today.)

38:26.461 --> 38:29.601
(How come we suddenly seem so familiar?)

38:29.822 --> 38:31.762
(He even told me about his whereabouts.)

38:36.382 --> 38:38.722
(I'm on the air. Let's talk later.)

38:48.379 --> 38:50.172
(Qiang Qingci)
(Login)

38:51.887 --> 38:54.236
(Shengshengman)

38:56.702 --> 38:59.477
Today, let's start
with the song Green Plums,

38:59.501 --> 39:03.162
because I just heard someone singing it.

39:06.530 --> 39:07.624
(Shengshengman)

39:07.624 --> 39:12.316
♪ Which sound soaks the green plums ♪

39:13.728 --> 39:18.236
♪ Which sound wrinkles the blue sky ♪

39:19.520 --> 39:23.720
♪ Shedding an invisible spring rain ♪

39:23.720 --> 39:30.268
♪ The world is drunk at a timid moment ♪

39:31.584 --> 39:36.348
♪ We talk and laugh
as if we are holding hands ♪

39:37.472 --> 39:43.752
♪ We stay silent
like falling behind the sunset ♪

39:43.752 --> 39:47.728
♪ That moment is still lingering ♪

39:47.728 --> 39:54.108
♪ When our eyes meet,
all vanish into nothing ♪

39:56.448 --> 40:02.891
♪ There seems to be a river
flowing through my heart ♪

40:03.168 --> 40:08.922
♪ Echoing with the constant gentleness
of the bright moon ♪

40:09.216 --> 40:11.912
♪ Looking back
among fleeting and everlasting moments ♪

40:11.912 --> 40:15.111
♪ We embrace as we look around ♪

40:15.111 --> 40:20.424
♪ Each sound is a promise of forever
to a lifetime ♪

40:20.424 --> 40:26.684
♪ It seems like you linger in my dreams
countless times ♪

40:27.200 --> 40:32.354
♪ Whenever I hear you,
my heart flutters a thousand times ♪

40:32.354 --> 40:36.008
♪ Birds fly past spring and autumn
once again ♪

40:36.008 --> 40:39.516
♪ The splendid world still remains ♪

40:40.000 --> 40:43.400
♪ Gifting us freedom ♪

40:43.400 --> 40:48.301
♪ We ferment each other into wine ♪

40:49.408 --> 40:55.688
♪ Within the intoxication, I can feel ♪

40:55.688 --> 40:59.891
♪ Your voice drifts across my heart ♪

40:59.891 --> 41:06.684
♪ Drifting through my life with no end ♪

41:06.822 --> 41:08.158
Are my eyes tricking me?

41:08.182 --> 41:10.162
The online audience
exceeded ten thousand.

41:11.150 --> 41:13.052
(Online members: 12007)

41:14.446 --> 41:15.021
(Qiang Qingci)

41:15.021 --> 41:18.202
Look. Isn't that Qiang Qingci?

41:18.262 --> 41:19.798
(Qiang Qingci)
Yes, it's him.

41:19.822 --> 41:21.421
It's really Qiang Qingci.

41:21.421 --> 41:23.641
Qiang Qingci has come
to our live broadcast.

41:24.718 --> 41:26.236
(Qiang Qingci)

41:26.782 --> 41:27.718
Isn't that right?

41:27.742 --> 41:28.838
Welcome.

41:28.862 --> 41:31.597
For our small club,
having a guest such as yourself

41:31.621 --> 41:33.121
is a great honor.

41:33.501 --> 41:35.981
I wonder if we could invite you
to our next singing event.

41:35.981 --> 41:37.500
What are you talking about?

41:39.902 --> 41:43.162
(If I'm not too busy with work,
I should be able to come.)

41:44.862 --> 41:46.678
That's my idol!

41:46.702 --> 41:48.117
Show some restraint.

41:48.141 --> 41:49.957
Sheng, say something.

41:49.981 --> 41:52.117
He is here as a guest.
We need to be hospitable.

41:52.141 --> 41:53.722
Reply to him.

41:54.141 --> 41:55.242
What should...

41:55.782 --> 41:57.902
I don't know how to play host.

41:57.902 --> 42:01.724
(Shengshengman)
(Interaction)

42:05.541 --> 42:07.041
- You two met in person?
- They did?

42:09.941 --> 42:11.957
But it wasn't just any meeting.

42:11.981 --> 42:14.238
It was for recording a song.

42:14.262 --> 42:17.402
- You two actually met in person?
- Right.

42:17.862 --> 42:19.718
But there were so many other people
at the scene.

42:19.742 --> 42:22.481
They were all
from the Perfect Voice Studio?

42:24.222 --> 42:26.678
Have you heard?
Isn't she just too lucky?

42:26.702 --> 42:28.838
Talk about that later.
Let Sheng greet our esteemed guest now.

42:28.862 --> 42:31.682
He is a rare guest.
We should entertain him properly.

42:32.222 --> 42:33.477
Entertain... Entertain...

42:33.501 --> 42:35.282
Sheng, the private message.

42:35.541 --> 42:36.517
The private message.

42:36.541 --> 42:39.182
Please give them some privacy.

42:39.182 --> 42:40.997
No wonder you can't find a girlfriend.

42:41.021 --> 42:42.117
Look quickly, Sheng.

42:42.141 --> 42:43.878
Qiang Qingci is looking for you
for something.

42:43.902 --> 42:46.441
If he suddenly contacts you,
it must be something important.

42:46.981 --> 42:48.397
It might not be him.

42:48.421 --> 42:50.402
Why don't you take a look?

42:50.501 --> 42:51.342
Let's go!

42:51.342 --> 42:52.101
What's wrong?

42:52.101 --> 42:54.041
We'll wait outside for you.

42:59.461 --> 43:02.641
(My phone is running out of power.
I just wanted to say hi to you.)

43:04.862 --> 43:05.862
(Okay.)

43:29.222 --> 43:30.158
It's all set?

43:30.182 --> 43:31.758
Listen and see if there are any issues.

43:31.782 --> 43:33.532
If there are problems, let me know.

43:39.501 --> 43:41.402
About that girl today,

43:41.941 --> 43:44.961
I heard you were quite special to her.

43:49.902 --> 43:50.917
Have you taken medicine?

43:50.941 --> 43:52.402
Of course.

43:53.101 --> 43:54.997
It's rare to find a girl you fall for.

43:55.021 --> 43:56.882
You have to put in extra effort.

43:57.021 --> 43:59.597
But you need to control
the degree and timing well.

43:59.621 --> 44:01.121
Don't be too forceful.

44:01.262 --> 44:02.722
Did you hear me?

44:06.342 --> 44:07.441
Let me hear.

44:16.262 --> 44:19.682
I sang several songs
during my live stream.

44:59.902 --> 45:05.302
♪ Turning the years into a drifting boat ♪

45:05.326 --> 45:10.412
♪ Sailing through
the tumult and winding sorrow ♪

45:10.670 --> 45:15.832
♪ I fear that the past will be crushed
by the coming cold wind ♪

45:15.832 --> 45:21.938
♪ And stirred into
a piece of tranquil river water ♪

45:24.270 --> 45:29.517
♪ Touching the crack with my fingertips ♪

45:29.517 --> 45:34.627
♪ I dare not look at the haggard faces
and gray hair in the mirror ♪

45:34.627 --> 45:40.344
♪ After many years,
the longing remains as sharp ♪

45:40.344 --> 45:45.866
♪ And our shadows are thinner ♪

45:45.866 --> 45:49.176
♪ Grinding the memories into ink ♪

45:49.176 --> 45:51.744
♪ And writing them on the paper ♪

45:51.744 --> 45:53.848
♪ The mirror and the person
are both gone ♪

45:53.848 --> 45:56.568
♪ Where could I ask for the return date ♪

45:56.568 --> 45:59.738
♪ The bronze mirror shatters at farewell ♪

45:59.738 --> 46:01.912
♪ It's hard to convey the lovesickness ♪

46:01.912 --> 46:06.540
♪ Over millions of miles ♪

46:07.118 --> 46:10.680
♪ I laugh at the fame
and wealth of my life ♪

46:10.680 --> 46:12.659
♪ I picture it as a flower in the mirror ♪

46:12.659 --> 46:17.784
♪ It's hard to rival
a cup of tea in your hand ♪

46:17.784 --> 46:19.416
♪ We drink from the same cup ♪

46:19.416 --> 46:21.368
♪ And we share joy and sorrow ♪

46:21.368 --> 46:24.221
♪ We drink down the past memories ♪

46:24.221 --> 46:28.888
♪ Being together from morning till night ♪

46:28.888 --> 46:32.248
♪ Or alone in the corner of the world ♪

46:32.248 --> 46:34.255
♪ Frost whitens the hair
in front of the forehead ♪

46:34.255 --> 46:39.416
♪ Looking at the world, where is my home ♪

46:39.416 --> 46:42.020
♪ I wish the clear frost
glitter in the moonlight ♪

46:42.020 --> 46:45.742
♪ Reflecting the couple in the mirror ♪

46:45.742 --> 46:50.828
♪ Return with you ♪

46:51.470 --> 46:57.142
♪ After being separated for half a life ♪
